Class DefaultDocker

    Docker
    public class DefaultDocker
extends java.lang.Object
implements Docker
    This is the default implementation of the Docker client which should provide all the features required.

        Create a container and retrieve the ID of the created container. Warning: if using stdin, you have to ensure that the command will in fact use stdin or else the call to getResult will return a Result with Result.isTimedOut() returning true
        Specified by:
        createContainer in interface Docker

        profileName - the name of the profile to look up. If a profile cannot be found, IllegalArgumentException will be thrown
        command - the command to run on the container
        bindings - any bindings for the container
        workingDirectory - the working directory for the container to work with
        stdin - the stdin input as a String. If Stdin is not required, pass in null or ""
        envs - environment variables to be set inside the docker container
        Returns:
        the ID of the created container
